  "title": "Core Concepts of Identifying Types of Gangs",
  "lessonText": "Understanding the various types of gangs is crucial in comprehending gang culture.",
  "data": {
    "content": "• Gangs can be categorized based on their activities, structure, and community influence.\n• Common types include:\n  - Street gangs: Often involved in local criminal activities and turf wars.\n  - Prison gangs: Formed within correctional facilities, often exerting influence outside.\n  - Motorcycle gangs: Typically organized around a shared interest in motorcycles, often associated with criminal enterprises.\n  - Drug gangs: Focused on the distribution and sale of illegal drugs.\n• Recognizing these types helps in understanding their impact on communities and the broader social implications.\n• Refer to the 'Exploring Elements of Gang Culture Walkthrough' for visual examples of these gang types and their characteristics."
  }
}
